        protected void postProcessBeanDefinition​(java.lang.Class<?> beanClass,
                                         java.lang.String beanId,
                                         boolean singleton,
                                         boolean lazyInit)
        Performs a post-processing of bean definitions when these are added to the bean container. Calls are delegated to registered bean extensions of type BeanExtension.
        Parameters:
        beanClass - the bean class that is added to the bean container
        beanId - the bean ID
        singleton - flag that indicates whether the bean is a singleton or not
        lazyInit - flag that indicates whether the bean is lazily initialized or not
